I’m happy to be a lone voice of positivity. I think if it was OK for Rian Johnson to up-end the apple-cart and subvert everything that had come before, then it should be OK for JJ Abrams to come back and try to right the cart and put the apples back in it. True, some of the apples are probably too bruised to be acceptable but overall, a quick wash and the apples taste great!


The ‘McGuffin hunt’ is a bad thing? I would claim it’s enough of a staple of Action-adventure/space-operas to not need to justify it’s use to further a plot, for reference see all of the Indiana Jones films and most of the Marvel and Bond films.

snippet.textDisplay:
Rian Johnson is not interested in the slightest with having a conversation with the fans, I have no idea how you could have gotten this impression unless you just don't pay attention at all to what he says and does. He's openly stated that there are no legitimate critcisms of his film out there and he has spent years now on twitter constantly antagonising the fans. At best you could call him a troll, but he's mostly just an asshole.


Bloodline has never been the sole factor of who can be a Jedi, who are Obi-wans parents? Mace Windu? Qui-Gon? Yoda? The only Jedi who had a blood line was Luke, 1 instance is not a trend. It's been open knowledge for an extremely long time in the EU that all living things are affected by the force and the force is running through them, but only certain people are 'force sensitive', meaning they have the ability to directly influence the force. These are not new concepts, they're only new to Disney's trilogy after they deleted the EU.


I'm not sure who you are talking about when you say "he's a fan, he loves these films". If its JJ, he's like the guy you go to with a giant bag of money and say "make a film, don't care if its faithful to the source", whereas Rian strikes me as someone that seems to at best be completely ignorant of Star Wars and at worst openly hostile towards it. His lack of knowledge when it comes to really basic elements of the universe is crazy, I'm not even sure he watched the OT.

snippet.textDisplay:
What pissed me off with this trilogy and what I'm hearing about TROS, is that they're so worried about looking to the original trilogy and their characters for some nostalgia, that they completely forget to write their own unique story with original characters.

If it were up to me, I'd have an absolutely new and original body of work that doesn't include the cast from the original trilogy. You have a WHOLE UNIVERSE of material to do and then they rip off the death star in TFA and then completely wreck the universe's established rules in TLJ.

MAKE SOMETHING NEW! Like, damn.. can we see a world where they actually expand on what there is to see except for some desert and snow planet??

I've got to say, not a great trilogy from what I've heard about the newest one.
snippet.textOriginal:
What pissed me off with this trilogy and what I'm hearing about TROS, is that they're so worried about looking to the original trilogy  and their characters for some nostalgia, that they completely forget to write their own unique story with original characters.

If it were up to me, I'd have an absolutely new and original body of work that doesn't include the cast from the original trilogy. You have a WHOLE UNIVERSE of material to do and then they rip off the death star in TFA and then completely wreck the universe's established rules in TLJ.

MAKE SOMETHING NEW! Like, damn.. can we see a world where they actually expand on what there is to see except for some desert and snow planet??

I've got to say, not a great trilogy from what I've heard about the newest one.

snippet.textDisplay:
The weird series of decisions started when Lucasfilm employed different directors for a series of canon films. Sure the original trilogy had different directors with Irvin Kershner and Richard Marquand on board...but first 3 films followed a firmly arranged canon story by Lucas himself.

If Lucasfilm really understood that JJ Abrams and Rian Johnson had different visions, they should build a main platform, a strong canon to begin with so if the director wants to play with the execution it doesn't stray too far from a cohesive base.

This trilogy will be better even a bit if Rian directed episode 9 as well (so no course correction needed, wrecked but at least cohesive) or JJ directed all 3 himself.

I was desperately hoping JJ wouldn't cave in to the toxic alt-right vocal minority of Star Wars fans, but here we are. This probably isn't the most those fans want, but it is the one they FUCKING DESERVE!



Just to clarify I'm not saying that every fan who hated The Last Jedi is toxic or alt-right, or even a minority (I think it's still very split). If you don't like The Last Jedi for legitimate reasons, that's fine. I've even started to agree with a few of those critiques (forced humor, uneven pacing, some characters are poorly developed). But the fans who verbally abuse people on social media or hate the movie because of politics, or the race/gender of main characters, or because Disney "killed their childhood, waaaa" can go eat a dick.
